<center><b>Halve</b> is a stylish, two-column jekyll theme.</center>
<p><br /></p>

<p>This theme is Jekyll port of <a href="http://vangeltzo.com/">vangeltzo.com</a> (by <a href="https://github.com/srekoble">Vangelis Tzortzis</a>). I couldn’t stop myself to port this theme when I saw his site. And he kindly gave me permission to share this with you.</p>

<iframe src="https://ghbtns.com/github-btn.html?user=TaylanTatli&amp;repo=Halve&amp;type=star&amp;count=true&amp;size=large" frameborder="0" scrolling="0" width="160px" height="30px"></iframe>

<h2 id="installation-and-quick-usage">Installation and Quick Usage</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Fork the <a href="https://github.com/TaylanTatli/Halve/fork">Halve repo</a></li>
  <li>Edit <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">_config.yml</code> file.</li>
  <li>Edit <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">index.md</code>.</li>
  <li>Edit <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">_data/projects.yaml</code></li>
  <li>Add a logo with a small one to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">images</code> folder. (eg. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">logo.png</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">logo-small.png</code>)</li>
  <li>Remove sample posts from <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">_posts</code> folder and add yours.</li>
  <li>Remove/Change sample images from <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">images</code> folder.</li>
  <li>Change repo name to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">YourUserName.github.io</code></li>
</ul>

<p>That’s all.</p>

<p>If you want to make a <strong>Project Page</strong>, you have to use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">gh-pages</code> branch. For <strong>Personal Page</strong>; <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">master</code> branch. More info <a href="https://help.github.com/articles/about-github-pages-and-jekyll/#jekylls-build-process">here</a>.</p>

