<h2 id="layouts-and-content">Layouts and Content</h2>

<p>Halve Theme use <a href="https://github.com/penibelst/jekyll-compress-html">Jekyll Compress</a> to compress html output. But it can cause errors if you use “linenos” (line numbers). I suggest don’t use line numbers for codes, because it won’t look good with this theme, also i didn’t give a proper style for them. If you insist to use line numbers, just remove <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">layout: compress</code> string from layouts. It will disable compressing.</p>

<h3 id="images-for-posts">Images for Posts</h3>

<p>You can set left block image per post. Just add <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">image: some link</code> to your post’s front matter. If you don’t set this, default post image will be used from <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">_config.yml</code>.</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>image: /assets/img/some-image.png
or
image: http://example.com/some-image.png
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>This also will be used for twitter card:</p>

<p><img src="http://localhost:4000/images/post-image-halve-5.png" alt="Halve Twitter Card" /></p>

